    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-12-05T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-12-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="80"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d80">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">701.6211/329½</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Wilson</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-12-05">
                            <hi rend="italic">5 December, 1915</hi>.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: No doubt you are right that
                    there is not sufficient evidence of acts here to base a demand for Albert’s
                    recall upon; but do you not think that there is evidence enough of his exercise
                    of authority and of his control of the evidently large sums of money which are
                    being spent in the country for purposes of non-neutral activity and outrages
                    against our peace? Since he is attached to the Germany Embassy we do not need
                    evidence enough to convict to justify us in saying that he is <hi rend="italic"
                        >persona non grata</hi>.</p>
                <p>Faithfully Yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>W. W.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
